Who I am & what I've been up to.

An Atlanta native who is looking to relocate to a new city and begin a job in a new role.

A few years ago I began working as a user experience and interface designer, what felt like a natural transition from my graphic design background into the tech industry. After completing a certificate course with Emory which comprised how to take a website from beginning stages of gathering assets and requirements to design, user testing, development and releasing the final product. Following the course, I spent some time freelancing on small sites and continuing learning where I could from online resources while looking for more stable full time work until getting a small contract position and eventually a longer contract with HLN, a subsidiary network to CNN. During my time there I assisted in redesigning and launching their website and was able to spend some time working with the development team and learn about their process. Upon finishing my contract with HLN, I went on to take a JavaScript course with General Assembly and soon after began working as UX/UI designer with Randstad. There I worked on web and mobile projects, as well as internal software to support job recruiters in searching for, maintaining and organizing, and communicating with clients and talent.

Over the course of working as a designer I have spent a portion of my free time staying acquainted with the direction of front end development trends and am now looking to make a transition into a full time development role. Coinciding with a shift in professional responsibilities, I am also seeking to relocate to a new state with a new landscape to take in and traverse.

My work.
